Interface IRepeatingGroupAccessor

    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public interface IRepeatingGroupAccessor
    An interface to access and manipulate FIX repeating groups from a containing store. When performing repeating group operations, a msgType, a dictionaryName and a parent store must be present on the accessor for validity checks. These checks can be:
    • Is the repeating group valid for the specified FIX message type according to the dictionary?
    • Does the first tag in the repeating group match the one in the dictionary?
    • Is a field valid for a particular repeating group?
    IFIXMessages are IRepeatingGroupAccessors. When IFIXMessages are created by a Sessions message factory, the default dictionary is set according to the FIX version/dictionary configured for that session. It is possible to specify custom dictionaries via the dictionaryName attribute of the Session (see Configuration_via_XML). RepeatingGroupEntry are also IRepeatingGroupAccessors to support nested repeating groups.

      • createRepeatingGroup

        @Deprecated
RepeatingGroup createRepeatingGroup(int groupTag)
                                         throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                                IllegalStateException
        Deprecated. 
        A new repeating group is created with the given numInGroup tag, added to the parent store, and returned.
        Parameters:
        groupTag - The tag identifying the repeating group according to the FIX spec (numInGroup tag)
        Returns:
        a repeating group with no entries (ie numInGroup tag = 0)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given tag is not valid for that particular message type according to the dictionary.
        IllegalStateException - If a group with the given tag already exists or if there's no message type or dictionary name specified.

      • setRepeatingGroup

        @Deprecated
void setRepeatingGroup(RepeatingGroup group)
                            throws IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Adds a pre-existing repeating group to the parent store. If the group with the given tag does not yet exist in the store it is created, otherwise the existing group will be cleaned and its contents replaced with the new group's content. General validations against the dictionary are performed.
        Parameters:
        group - Group to set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the passed in repeating group is not valid for the parent store based on msg type and dictionary.
